Introduced
Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE CONCURRENT
RESOLUTION No. _____
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION celebrating the legacy
2 of Abigail "Abby" Williams and Liberty "Libby" German.
3 Whereas, Students at Delphi Community Middle School in
4 Delphi, Indiana, Abby and Libby were more like sisters than
5 friends and followed each other wherever the other went;
6 Whereas, Both girls were on the volleyball team, played in
7 the middle school band, and had almost all of their
8 extracurricular activities aligned with each other;
9 Whereas, Libby aspired to be a forensic scientist to help the
10 police solve crimes and loved arts and crafts, spending time
11 going on adventures, and vacationing with family;
12 Whereas, Abby enjoyed reading, photography, spending
13 time outdoors, and loved all animals, particularly her cat,
14 Bongo;
15 Whereas, The Abby and Libby Memorial Park opened in
16 Delphi in 2021 with an inaugural softball tournament in honor
17 of these two young girls whose lives were taken far too soon;
18 and
19 Whereas, The legacy Abby and Libby have left behind will
20 inspire future generations to live with purpose and play with
21 passion: Therefore,
22 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly
23 of the State of Indiana, the House of Representatives
2026 RC 1530/DI JR

2
1 concurring:
2 SECTION 1. That the Indiana General Assembly celebrates
3 the life and legacy of Abby and Libby.
4 SECTION 2. The Secretary of the Senate is hereby directed
5 to transmit copies of this Resolution to the families of Abby
6 Williams and Libby German.
2026 RC 1530/DI JR

